<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1939-07-13T12:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1939-07-13T12:00:00-05:00" n="233" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d233">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">715.1715/1447: Telegram</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The Assistant to the Representative of the
                                    President</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Ocheltree</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                                </hi>
                            </head>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">San José</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1939-07-13T11:00:00-06:00">July
                                        13, 1939—11 a.m.</date>
                                    <lb/> [Received 1:30 p.m.]</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>7. Referring to Department’s telegram No. 34, July 11, 7 p.m.,
                                Licenciado Zúñiga Montúfar has consented to my visiting Tegucigalpa
                                in connection with the mediation and has agreed to setting October
                                1st as a tentative date for an executive session of the
                                Commission.</p>
                            <p>I am proceeding to Tegucigalpa by plane tomorrow.</p>
                            <p>With reference to the Department’s telegram No. 35,<note n="37" xml:id="d233fn37">Telegram No. 35, July 12, 7 p.m., contained
                                    travel orders (715.1715/1445b suppl.).</note> please inform me
                                at Tegucigalpa whether airplane travel to Washington is
                                authorized.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Ocheltree</hi>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>